entries.description: Greg Bertz, 69, was cited for drug possession on December 16 and is set to appear in court on January 2, 2023, after a hospital worker at Hays Medical Center caught him vaping.

entries.title: 35 killed nationwide from devastating winter storm - 13 dead in Western New York alone
entries.description: The rising death toll comes as parts of New York are preparing for upwards of 30 inches through Tuesday. The ages of those killed in Buffalo and the surrounding areas range from 26 to 93.

entries.title: Boxing Day shoppers out for a bargain warned they will face traffic chaos as train strikes continue
entries.description: Boxing Day bargain hunters set to hit the high streets today have been warned that they could face severe traffic jams as Britain's railways shut down for strike action for the second day running.

entries.title: Mother who was told her baby had died gives birth after 'gut feeling' told her doctors were wrong
entries.description: Hannah Cole, 27, was admitted to the Bradford Royal Infirmary (BRI) after her waters broke early at 20 weeks. While doctors told her that the baby had died, gut instinct made her think this was not true.

entries.title: London exodus is slowing down as 20,000 fewer properties were bought outside the capital
entries.description: Estate agency Hamptons estimates that Londoners have purchased around 81,200 properties away from the city this year, down from 100,540 in 2021.

entries.title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: A wise speech straight from the King's heart
entries.description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: After seven decades, the Queen's annual Christmas Day message had become as synonymous with the festive season as turkey and mince pies.

entries.title: Idaho victim Maddie Mogen's dad convinced murderer made mistake that will lead to their capture
entries.description: Idaho victim Maddie Mogen's dad Ben Mogen says he is  convinced the killer made a mistake at the scene that will lead to their capture, but admits he is surprised he is 'still waiting' for answers.

entries.title: Sydney to Hobart yacht race: Model Lisa Seiffert sets sail despite breast cancer diagnosis
entries.description: An Australian model who fought through a cancer diagnosis, radiotherapy and surgery all within six weeks is set to embark on one of the world's toughest yacht races.

entries.title: Families face more money misery as fraudsters could steal £76m during festive period
entries.description: More than £6 million a day is lost to internet scammers on average, with 312 instances of online fraud or cyber crime a day over the past two years.

entries.title: Princess of Wales tells young fan that her children got 'lots of lovely things' for Christmas
entries.description: The young fan, named India, was filmed giving the Princess a bouquet of flowers as the Royal Family joined King Charles yesterday on his walkabout outside Sandringham church.

entries.title: Tesla is set to have its worst year EVER as car firm's share price slumps by 70% in 13 months
entries.description: Tesla shares are down 64% for the year, potentially marking their worst annual performance since going public in 2010. Musk sold $2.58 billion worth of Tesla stock last week.

entries.title: NHS bosses spend £65million a year on prescriptions for items such as bread and SHAMPOO
entries.description: Health chiefs had promised to cut down on wasteful prescriptions in 2018 but the amount spent on providing household goods has risen by nearly half since before the pandemic.

entries.title: NHS bosses want interview panels to justify why they have hired a white person
entries.description: Woke NHS bosses are forcing interview panels to explain why they have hired a white person over someone from an ethnic minority, the Daily Mail can reveal.

entries.title: Another seasonal story from our lovable rogue, to celebrate a centenary of Just William
entries.description: William walked slowly and thoughtfully down the village street. It was the week after Christmas. Henry was still away. Douglas and Ginger were the only two of his friends left in the village.

entries.title: Camilla's guest-edited edition of Country Life becomes biggest-selling issue ever
entries.description: The edition, which featured a photograph of Camilla taken by the Princess of Wales and told of her own strong bond with the UK's natural environment, sold nearly 70,000 copies.

entries.title: Kings County receives Ebenezer Award over woke edict banning Christmas or Hannukah displays
entries.description: King County, which encompasses Seattle, was the recipient of this year's award from the Becket Fund for Religious Liberty due to its 'Guidelines for Holiday Decorations,' the group said in a statement.

entries.title: Four-year-old strolls into Santa's grotto unaided a year after cancer confined her to a wheelchair
entries.description: After cancer left her in a wheelchair, Yasmin Roper's main wish this Christmas was to be able to walk into Santa's grotto by herself. And last week the four-year-old defied the odds to achieve it.

entries.title: Florida sheriff's deputy fatally shot on Christmas Eve responding to domestic violence suspect
entries.description: Florida sheriff's deputy Cpl. Ray Hamilton was fatally shot by Timothy Price Wiliams, 43, Christmas Eve while he was responding to a domestic violence assault.

entries.title: Firm linked to husband of 'Baroness Bra' Michelle Mone lavishes £10m on Belgravia townhouse
entries.description: Michelle Mone's husband (both pictured) property in Belgravia - one of London's most exclusive areas - was bought in December 2020 by Chester Ventures weeks after it was incorporated.

entries.title: Florida man allegedly beat five-month-old Goldendoodle to death
entries.description: A trial date has been set for the Florida man accused of beating his five-month-old Goldendoodle, 'Buzz Lightyear,' to death.

entries.title: LA pastor foster mom struck and killed by hit-and-run driver while giving out Christmas presents
entries.description: Trina Newman, 61, a dedicated activist and minister, was tragically hit by a car while dropping off presents for local kids at a community center in South Los Angeles.
